  <Subject Subject_ID="300265783">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300193855</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>conditions and effects for textiles [300193855], conditions and effects by specific type [300389722], Conditions and Effects (hierarchy name) [300186269], Physical Attributes Facet [300264087]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a textile effect produced by weaving warp threads of one color and weft threads of a contrasting color, so that the fabric, often silk or other lustrous fabric, changes in color when viewed from different points of view.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051926/Maitra, Encyclopaedic Dictionary of Clothing and Textiles (1997)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refiere a un efecto del textil producido tejiendo los hilos de un color y los hilos de otro color que se pone en contraste, de modo que la tela, a menudo seda u otra tela brillante, tienen cambios en el color desde diversos puntos de vista.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar een effect bij textiel dat ontstaat door het weven van scheringdraden in één kleur en inslagdraden in een contrasterende kleur. Gevolg is dat de stof, vaak zijde of een andere glimmende stof, van kleur verandert wanneer deze vanuit een ander gezichtspunt wordt bekeken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052403/Van Dale Groot Woordenboek (1998)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>意指將某顏色之經紗及其對比色之緯紗交織而成的織品效果，此布料通常為絲或其他具光澤的布料，從不同角度看時顏色會改變。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
